Code Implementation Guidelines (Follow these rules strictly when writing code):

    1.	Component Structure

    Use const arrow functions for components (e.g., const Form = () => {...}).

    Define explicit TypeScript types for props/state (e.g., type FormProps = { sessionId: string }).

    Use named exports only (e.g., export const SuggestionsGrid = () => {...}).


Performance & Readability

Prioritize readability over optimization (e.g., avoid premature memoization).

Use early returns for conditional rendering (e.g., if (!data) return <Loading />;).

Split large components into smaller, reusable subcomponents (e.g., SuggestionsCard).

State & Event Handling

Prefix event handlers with handle (e.g., handleSubmit, handleSocialLinkChange).

Use useState/useReducer for local state; avoid unnecessary global state.

Debounce API calls in forms (e.g., lodash.debounce for social link input).

Project-Specific Rules

All buttons/inputs must use ui.shadcn components (e.g., <Button variant="primary">).

Mock AI/data APIs with static responses until Stage 4 (e.g., MOCK_SUGGESTIONS).

Enforce mobile-first design: use max-w-[480px] for modals and md: breakpoints.

File Structure

Components: /client/src/components/[ComponentName]/ (e.g., Form.tsx, index.ts).

Types: /client/src/types.ts for global type definitions.

Utils: /client/src/utils/ for helpers (e.g., formatConfidenceScore).

Linting & Formatting

Use 2-space indentation, trailing commas, and semicolons.

Alphabetize imports (React first, external deps next, internal last).